---
import { CONTROLLER, PLATFORM_NAME } from "astro:env/client";
import ArticleLayout from "#src/layouts/Article.astro";
import emails from "#shared/email.json";
---

<ArticleLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <!-- <meta name="robots" content="noindex" /> -->
  </Fragment>

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p>
    <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> is committed to protecting your privacy. This platform does not track users for advertising or analytics.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data collected by the platform</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account data:</strong> email addresses, contact names, passkeys, OAuth IDs...</li>
    <li><strong>Profile content:</strong> links, text, images...</li>
    <li><strong>Reports:</strong> reported profiles, email addresses and names of reporters, messages...</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data collected by third-parties</h2>
  <p>
    Technical data is processed by <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >Cloudflare</a
    > (IP and browser information for security purposes).
  </p>
  <p>
    Microsoft Azure Email Communication Services is the service used to send transactional emails to users. They may process or even
    blacklist email addresses that resulted in a hard bounce or spam complaints.
  </p>
  <p>Payments inside the platform are handled by <a href="https://polar.sh/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polar.sh</a>.</p>
  <p>
    Profiles may embed content from third parties (e.g., YouTube, Spotify). When you visit a profile containing an iframe and agree to
    display them, these third parties may process your IP address and set cookies. <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> does not control these third
    parties; please refer to their respective privacy policies. For full details on cookies see the <a href="/i/cookie">Cookie Policy</a> page.
  </p>
  <p>
    This website, <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> platform and user profiles may display links to external websites, whose privacy practices
    <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> is not responsible for.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contract performance</strong> (account creation, profiles).</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> (security via Cloudflare).</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> (tax, anti-fraud).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data storage and processors</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Hosting:</strong>
      <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Azure</a> - Spain Central and North Europe
      (Ireland)
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Images:</strong>
      <a href="https://www.backblaze.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Backblaze B2</a> - EU Central (Amsterdam)
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>CDN:</strong>
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare</a> and <a
        href="https://www.jsdelivr.com/terms/privacy-policy"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">jsDelivr</a
      >
    </li>
    <li><strong>Payments:</strong> <a href="https://polar.sh/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polar.sh</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Your GDPR rights</h2>
  <p>Access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, objection, and withdrawal of consent.</p>
  <p>Contact: <a href={`mailto:${emails.contact}`}>{emails.contact}</a></p>

  <h2>6. Public profiles and external archiving</h2>
  <p>Profiles are public by default and they are accessible to anyone on the internet. As a result, their content may be:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Indexed by search engines (Google, Bing, etc.).</li>
    <li>Archived by third-party services such as the Internet Archive (Wayback Machine) or similar public archiving tools.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> does not control these external services and cannot guarantee that content will be removed from them, even
    if you delete a profile later. By creating a profile, you acknowledge and accept that its content may remain publicly available and archived
    indefinitely.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    If your account was not active for 6 years, <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> may email you to ask if you want to keep your account. If you
    do not respond within 30 days, the account will be deleted, along with all associated profiles with no other members.
  </p>
  <p>After you delete or update content in your account or profiles, it may take a few minutes for those changes to become visible.</p>
  <p>When an account is deleted, some data can remain in the <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> systems for up to 15 days.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> may blacklist email addresses that resulted in a hard bounce or spam complaints. If you think your email
    address was blacklisted by mistake, you can contact at <a href={`mailto:${emails.contact}`}>{emails.contact}</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    When a report is made to a profile, the report information will remain in the <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> systems for up to 15 days after
    the report is resolved.
  </p>
  <p>A user who has been banned remains in the system from 15 days to 180 days, depending on the severity of the ban.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes or legal requirements. Material changes will be notified to
    registered users.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p class="p-controller">{CONTROLLER}</p>

  <p>For full details on cookies see the <a href="/i/cookie">Cookie Policy</a> page.</p>

  <p>For information regarding the governing law and jurisdiction, please refer to the <a href="/i/legal-notice">Legal Notice</a> page.</p>

  <p>Last updated: April 2026</p>
</ArticleLayout>

<style>
  .p-controller {
    user-select: none !important;
  }
</style>
